---
import SectionHead from './SectionHead.astro';
---

<section id="about">
	<div class="wrap">
		<SectionHead num="§ 01 / About" title="A few" titleEm="things about me." />
		<div class="about-grid">
			<aside class="about-side">
				<div class="about-side-block">
					<span class="k">Now</span>
					<span class="v">Shipping at a mid-sized startup</span>
				</div>
				<div class="about-side-block">
					<span class="k">Reading</span>
					<span class="v">Designing Data-Intensive Applications</span>
				</div>
				<div class="about-side-block">
					<span class="k">Hobbies</span>
					<div class="v-list">
						<span>Cycling</span>
						<span>Bouldering</span>
						<span>Writing essays</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="about-side-block">
					<span class="k">Languages</span>
					<div class="v-list">
						<span>English</span>
						<span>Mandarin</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</aside>
			<div class="about-body">
				<p>
					I'm a software engineer based in New York. I grew up planning every detail of my life and
					then slowly learned that <strong>you will never feel like you're ready</strong> — you can only
					start being ready. Most of the best things I've done came from starting before I felt prepared.
				</p>
				<p>
					Professionally I work on backend systems — the boring, load-bearing kind. I like problems
					where a small change unlocks a big win: a query plan you can cut in half, a protocol you
					can simplify, a runbook that turns a 2 AM page into a 10-minute fix.
				</p>
				<p>
					Away from the keyboard I cycle long routes out of the city, fall off bouldering problems I
					have no business attempting, and write short essays about <strong
						>responsibility, readiness, and the gifts of the era we live in</strong
					>. If any of that resonates, say hello.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
